How to Start the Project
Follow the steps below to set up and run the project:

1. Set Up Virtual Environment
First, create and activate a virtual environment:

bash
Copy
Edit
python -m venv venv
Activate the virtual environment:

On Windows:
bash
Copy
Edit
.\venv\Scripts\Activate
On macOS/Linux:
bash
Copy
Edit
source venv/bin/activate
2. Install Dependencies
Install the required dependencies:

bash
Copy
Edit
pip install -r requirements.txt
3. Set Up and Start Docker Containers
Navigate to the docker directory and start the Docker containers using docker-compose:

bash
Copy
Edit
cd docker
docker-compose up --build
Project Structure
Here is the file structure of the project:

bash
Copy
Edit
3_API/
│
├── app/
│   ├── __init__.py
│   ├── config/
│   │   ├── __init__.py
│   │   └── config.py
│   ├── model.py
│   ├── routes.py
│   └── __init__.py  # Initialize app and db in this file
│
├── docker/
│   ├── postgres/
│   │   └── init.sql  # Database schema initialization file
│   └── docker-compose.yml  # Defines Docker services
│
├── venv/               # Virtual Environment
├── .env                # Environment variables (keep sensitive info here)
├── .gitignore          # Git ignore file
├── Dockerfile          # Docker container setup
└── requirements.txt    # Python dependencies